G-MOE-GPU2-EXPERTS — GPU residency rung 2: resident experts via view DevTensors (2026-07-02)
============================================================================================
BUILT:
- q36_expert_view (cuda_forward.cu): an expert's matmul = a VIEW DevTensor over the whole
  uploaded rank-3 tensor — row_off is ABSOLUTE into codes, so the view just offsets the
  row_off/row_prec/row_scale/bscale pointers and sets out to the slice height. NO new GEMV
  kernels; the dp4a path runs unchanged on the slice.
- sp_q36gpu_upload_experts / sp_q36gpu_moe: per layer, gate/up/down uploaded whole; a MoE
  call = H2D x once -> per expert (gate GEMV + up GEMV + k_silu_mul + down GEMV +
  dg_k_axpy weighted accumulate) ALL ASYNC -> ONE stream sync -> D2H y. (k_silu_mul and
  dg_k_axpy reused from the diffusion campaign; SiLU matches qwen36 exactly.)
- Math-core: sp_moe_register_ext hook — moe_ffn calls it AFTER the (never-quantized) f32
  CPU router top-k, keyed by the gate-experts tensor name; 0 = routed sum done on GPU
  (shared expert stays CPU), nonzero = layer not resident -> CPU experts. Unregistered =
  null floor. PARTIAL RESIDENCY falls out for free: resident layers hit GPU, the rump CPU.
- Harness: budget-driven upload from layer 0 (QWEN36_GPU_MOE_GB, default 8.5).

GATE (35B OK-container, greedy 16, step+GPU): SEQ IDENTICAL 21/21 at BOTH budgets tested
(22 and 26 resident layers). The sequence has now survived: scalar-serial, OMP, AVX2,
batched, GPU-dense-dp4a, and GPU-expert-dp4a arithmetic — unchanged at every rung.
VERDICT: **GREEN**.

RESIDENCY + LADDER (i9-11900KB + RTX 2060 12GB):
  budget 8.5GB: 22/40 expert layers resident (8.4GB)  -> 3.412 tok/s
  budget 9.9GB: 26/40 expert layers resident (10.0GB) -> 3.824 tok/s  (card at ~10.8GB)
  stateless 0.018 | +state 0.165 | +OMP 1.136 | +SIMD 1.605 | +batch 1.655
  | +GPU dense 3.312 | +GPU experts **3.824** = **212x CUMULATIVE** (~0.26s/token flat)

PROFILE (22-layer run): moe 68% of step — DECOMPOSED: resident layers ~0.8ms each on GPU
(7x cheaper than CPU's ~6ms/layer); the wall is the NON-resident rump (18 layers CPU) +
conv+recurrence now 22% (scalar CPU, rising as everything else shrinks).

GPU-3 (pre-scoped): (1) STREAM the rump layers' 8 selected experts per token (~10MB/layer
over PCIe into a preallocated device slab + pinned staging — est ~2ms/layer vs ~6ms CPU);
(2) thread/SIMD the GDN conv+recurrence (now-visible 2nd wall); (3) move the argmax on-device
(k_argmax exists) + keep logits resident; (4) LRU expert swapping only if routing locality
proves poor (measure hit-rates first — routing entropy decides streaming vs LRU).
RUNTIME GOTCHA (recurring): the exe needs BOTH env-cuda PATH (cudart/cublas) AND LLVM bin
(libomp DLL) — 0xC0000135 silent death otherwise; receipted twice now, bake into any launcher.
ENV: engine + submodule this-commit; clang-cl /openmp /arch:AVX2 /DQ36_GPU + backend nvcc.
Raw: _gen_gpu2.out (22L), _gen_gpu2d.out (26L), _prof4.err.
